Package: qwertywm
Architecture: amd64
Depends: river (>= 0.4), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Dynamic tiling window manager for river
 qwertywm is an xmonad-style dynamic tiling window manager that runs
 on top of the river Wayland compositor. It features:
  * Master/stack tiling with configurable ratio, count, and location
  * Monocle mode
  * Floating and fullscreen windows
  * Multi-output support with directional focus
  * Programmatic control over a unix socket (qwertywmctl)
  * Keyboard-driven workflow
  * Independent or locked workspace modes
